1
00:00:11,791 --> 00:00:13,083
[alarm ringing]

2
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:18,000
[groans]

3
00:00:18,083 --> 00:00:19,208
[groans]

4
00:00:19,291 --> 00:00:22,708
[YUKI]
Get up, Arata! Rise and shine!

5
00:00:23,708 --> 00:00:25,458
[alarm continues]

6
00:00:28,583 --> 00:00:29,416
-[ARATA grunts]
-[alarm stops]

7
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,458
Oh, hello. Good morning!

8
00:00:35,458 --> 00:00:37,916
-Uh. You're here?
-That's right.

9
00:00:39,916 --> 00:00:41,916
I thought it would be wise
to attempt to blend in

10
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,708
with the humans of this era.

11
00:00:43,791 --> 00:00:45,875
What do you think
of this outfit I found?

12
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:47,333
Or would you prefer to see me

13
00:00:47,416 --> 00:00:48,916
in something
a little bit more masculine?

14
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,958
I, uh... I don't care.
Wear what you want.

15
00:00:53,958 --> 00:00:56,000
Are you going to explain
to me why you're here?

16
00:00:56,083 --> 00:00:57,250
[COYOTE]
Should I not be?

17
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:58,416
[ARATA]
Well, it's my place.

18
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,375
I realize that.

19
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:03,541
Is there a reason you don't want
me floating around your home?

20
00:01:03,625 --> 00:01:05,833
You allow that cat
to stay here.

21
00:01:05,916 --> 00:01:07,041
Why not me?

22
00:01:07,125 --> 00:01:08,916
I'm Arata's friend, thank you.

23
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,791
[ARATA sighs]

24
00:01:10,875 --> 00:01:12,833
If I told you
I value my privacy,

25
00:01:12,916 --> 00:01:14,250
would that make sense?

26
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:16,708
We never used
to keep secrets from each other.

27
00:01:16,791 --> 00:01:18,083
Rude.

28
00:01:20,375 --> 00:01:22,166
[ARATA]
Well, if you're not gonna leave,

29
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:24,250
why don't you tell me more
about this Seimei?

30
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,541
You want me to tell you
about the past?

31
00:01:26,625 --> 00:01:29,083
That's such a typical thing
for a human to request.

32
00:01:29,166 --> 00:01:32,666
Even more so to ask a friend
for stories about yourself.

33
00:01:32,750 --> 00:01:34,708
It's not like that.
How would I know?

34
00:01:34,791 --> 00:01:36,083
[chuckles]

35
00:01:36,166 --> 00:01:38,583
I'll make an exception
if you forgot.

36
00:01:38,666 --> 00:01:40,166
And it seems you have.

37
00:01:40,250 --> 00:01:43,250
♪

38
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:44,583
[SEIMEI] You expect me
to believe you're from

39
00:01:44,666 --> 00:01:46,500
a world underneath us?

40
00:01:46,583 --> 00:01:49,708
Yes, I do.
Please, allow me to explain.

41
00:01:49,791 --> 00:01:53,208
♪

42
00:01:53,291 --> 00:01:56,250
We are standing
on this part of the world.

43
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:58,833
And I am from an area
over here.

44
00:01:58,916 --> 00:02:01,708
You mean the world we live in
is round like that?

45
00:02:01,791 --> 00:02:05,041
If so, wouldn't those
at the bottom fall off?

46
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,083
They're wondering
why you don't fall.

47
00:02:07,166 --> 00:02:09,000
To them,
you're on the bottom side.

48
00:02:09,083 --> 00:02:10,250
[chuckles]

49
00:02:10,333 --> 00:02:11,958
I admit, that is fascinating.

50
00:02:12,041 --> 00:02:13,250
You're a good storyteller.

51
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:15,083
[COYOTE]
Well, there's more.

52
00:02:15,166 --> 00:02:17,041
Did you know that the stars
are in a different order

53
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:18,625
to those living
in other countries?

54
00:02:18,708 --> 00:02:20,541
Does that mean
they get lost more often?

55
00:02:22,708 --> 00:02:26,250
You had such a thirst
for knowledge those days.

56
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:28,708
Wait, that means someone
from the Heian period

57
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:30,625
knew earth was round
before we did.

58
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:32,000
Yes, that's true.

59
00:02:32,083 --> 00:02:33,291
That someone insisted on

60
00:02:33,375 --> 00:02:34,458
learning about the stars.

61
00:02:34,541 --> 00:02:36,000
-Don't you remember?
-Oh, crap!

62
00:02:36,083 --> 00:02:37,541
I gotta go! I'll be late!

63
00:02:37,625 --> 00:02:39,458
[scampering footsteps]

64
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:45,250
Always in such a hurry.

65
00:04:17,583 --> 00:04:18,875
[KYOICHI]
Okay, then.

66
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:21,000
Any news on
the old Coyote situation?

67
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:22,125
[ARATA]
Not really.

68
00:04:22,208 --> 00:04:23,750
Then let's table
that case for now,

69
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,500
since no one seems
to be in danger.

70
00:04:25,583 --> 00:04:26,916
[THEO]
Agreed.

71
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,583
Unless there's
a good enough reason,

72
00:04:28,666 --> 00:04:30,958
you don't want to try
and tackle a god of calamity.

73
00:04:31,958 --> 00:04:35,250
Let's not call him a god.
I'd say he's more like a NEET.

74
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:37,583
I can't imagine
what's happening in his mind.

75
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:40,083
[THEO] Don't try.
That would be like trying

76
00:04:40,166 --> 00:04:42,166
to figure out
what motivates a typhoon.

77
00:04:42,250 --> 00:04:45,083
You'd be wasting your time,
and you'd drive yourself mad.

78
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:47,500
[ARATA] A typhoon?
Yeah, I can see that.

79
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:49,458
[YUKI grunts]

80
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,916
The look on your face!
Cats are so funny!

81
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,000
[YUKI]
Shut up!

82
00:04:58,541 --> 00:05:01,208
Well, we should still keep
an eye on him.

83
00:05:01,291 --> 00:05:02,958
Yeah, definitely.

84
00:05:03,041 --> 00:05:05,250
We might learn something
we'll need later.

85
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:08,083
Good morning.

86
00:05:08,166 --> 00:05:10,291
-Morning. Good to see you.
-[door closes]

87
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:11,625
[KYOICHI]
How's it going, Senda?

88
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:13,208
[SENDA]
Great!

89
00:05:13,291 --> 00:05:14,750
[sighs]

90
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:17,000
Hey, guys. Your reports?

91
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:19,208
I'm assuming you're about ready
to turn those in to me?

92
00:05:19,291 --> 00:05:20,625
What reports?

93
00:05:20,708 --> 00:05:22,166
[SENDA]
Don't mess with me right now.

94
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:24,125
Same report
we turn in every year.

95
00:05:24,208 --> 00:05:25,625
You need to have them
in tomorrow.

96
00:05:27,583 --> 00:05:30,250
[THEO] Wow, already?
Time flies, doesn't it?

97
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,333
The Shinjuku Ward Special Cases

98
00:05:32,416 --> 00:05:35,000
Fixed-Point Observation
isn't new.

99
00:05:35,083 --> 00:05:37,000
[THEO]
But it's such a pain in the ass!

100
00:05:37,083 --> 00:05:39,625
[SENDA] I know.
I've done it. On time.

101
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:42,083
We're outside today,
so hurry up.

102
00:05:42,166 --> 00:05:43,916
[THEO sighs]
Fine. I'm on it.

103
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,291
Where are we going?

104
00:05:45,375 --> 00:05:46,833
[KYOICHI]
It's right over there.

105
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:49,041
♪

106
00:05:49,125 --> 00:05:50,541
You mean Kabukicho?

107
00:05:50,625 --> 00:05:53,250
Yep. They want reports
on six Anothers

108
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:55,125
who are apparently living here.

109
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:56,541
In case there are any issues.

110
00:05:57,541 --> 00:06:00,041
It's pretty much become
a tradition for our section.

111
00:06:01,291 --> 00:06:03,458
Let's see, number two
are the shojo.

112
00:06:03,541 --> 00:06:05,833
Number three's Minerva's Owl.

113
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:07,958
Number four's a dryad.

114
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:10,041
Mezu is five.

115
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:11,625
Number six is Bultungin.

116
00:06:12,666 --> 00:06:14,583
And Azukiarai is number seven.

117
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,083
Um, what happened
to number one?

118
00:06:17,166 --> 00:06:18,833
We've got enough with these six

119
00:06:18,916 --> 00:06:20,416
without digging
into whatever's going on

120
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,583
with that one.

121
00:06:21,666 --> 00:06:22,625
[KYOICHI]
Exactly.

122
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:24,416
-Stay focused, Miyako.
-Right!

123
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,750
♪

124
00:06:34,625 --> 00:06:35,791
[KYOICHI]
Let's get started, shall we?

125
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:36,708
[THEO]
Right behind you.

126
00:06:36,791 --> 00:06:38,583
Smells like alcohol.

127
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:40,166
[SHOJO 1]
Come on! Keep drinking!

128
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:41,833
[SHOJO 2]
Hey, it's my second bottle!

129
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:44,208
[SHOJO 1] How 'bout
that catch we made, huh?

130
00:06:44,291 --> 00:06:46,875
They sound angry.
What's going on with them?

131
00:06:46,958 --> 00:06:48,166
What are you lookin' at?

132
00:06:48,250 --> 00:06:50,750
You got a problem,
Neck Tie and Four Eyes?

133
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:54,041
-They're gorillas?
-Shojo.

134
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:56,916
A type of Monkey Another
originally from ancient China.

135
00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:01,041
[growling, sniffing]

136
00:07:02,291 --> 00:07:03,791
[SHOJO 1]
You smell like rookie meat.

137
00:07:04,875 --> 00:07:06,500
[chuckling]

138
00:07:06,583 --> 00:07:09,000
[SHOJO 2] All I can smell
are my sake burps

139
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:11,666
-So, uh, you guys cops?
-Not at all!

140
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:14,000
Shinjuku Ward civil servants!

141
00:07:14,083 --> 00:07:16,583
This guy just answered
like he understood what we said!

142
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:19,291
I know! He must be
that Ears of Sand guy!

143
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:20,500
Uh...

144
00:07:20,583 --> 00:07:23,833
He's just like
any other stupid human!

145
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:26,458
But maybe that could make
things more fun around here.

146
00:07:26,541 --> 00:07:28,833
We've been drinking with the
same group since Gongen left,

147
00:07:28,916 --> 00:07:30,291
and I'm getting bored.

148
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:31,916
[ARATA]
Who's Gongen?

149
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,000
[SHOJO 1]
All right, this one's for you.

150
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:36,500
-Oh. That's okay, please don't.
-[SHOJO 2] Why not?

151
00:07:36,583 --> 00:07:38,666
Our sake's
not good enough for you?

152
00:07:39,708 --> 00:07:41,041
[SHOJO 1]
Try it!

153
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:43,541
Throw it back!
You're gonna love it!

154
00:07:43,625 --> 00:07:45,166
[chuckles nervously]

155
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:46,708
Just one.

156
00:07:46,791 --> 00:07:48,166
[THEO]
Are you an idiot?

157
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:50,041
Uh? You didn't drink it.

158
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:52,791
Maybe next time.
I'm still working.

159
00:07:52,875 --> 00:07:55,666
Work? Is that what
you do for money?

160
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:57,708
For more drinks?

161
00:07:57,791 --> 00:07:59,000
[KYOICHI]
Don't ever put something

162
00:07:59,083 --> 00:08:00,666
an Another gives you
close to your mouth!

163
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:03,250
Understood.
They were being nice, though.

164
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:05,583
Anothers don't really think
in the terms of "nice."

165
00:08:05,666 --> 00:08:07,208
They were probably trying
to loosen you up

166
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:09,750
to make it easier for them
when they get hungry.

167
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:11,833
Huh? What do you mean by that?

168
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:13,375
[KYOICHI]
He means they'd eat you.

169
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:16,916
They've been there for a year
just hanging out with each other

170
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,333
and getting wasted.

171
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:19,750
Huh.

172
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,333
We don't know if
they're planning on leaving

173
00:08:21,416 --> 00:08:23,458
or if they're there
permanently or what.

174
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:26,125
That's why we have to keep
checking in on them regularly.

175
00:08:27,125 --> 00:08:29,083
[ARATA] If they've been
wasted for a year,

176
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:31,083
how'd they hear about
the Ears of Sand?

177
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:34,083
♪

178
00:08:34,166 --> 00:08:37,958
Wow, this is amazing!
I got my wallet back!

179
00:08:38,041 --> 00:08:40,083
Yeah, glad we could
help you out!

180
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:41,708
There's some paperwork
for you to sign

181
00:08:41,791 --> 00:08:43,666
just so it's on file
that you picked it up.

182
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,000
[MAN]
Cool, cool!

183
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:47,583
Hey, Nakamura,
he's ready for you.

184
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:48,625
On it!

185
00:08:49,666 --> 00:08:50,625
[KYOICHI]
Hello, Haguro.

186
00:08:50,708 --> 00:08:52,000
-You got a minute?
-Huh?

187
00:08:52,083 --> 00:08:53,541
[HAGURO]
Sakaki. Of course.

188
00:08:54,583 --> 00:08:57,000
If you could just
sign here please.

189
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:59,000
All right. No problem!

190
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,166
They were here and here.

191
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,000
They moved
a little further than before,

192
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:07,500
but, other than that,
nothing else to report.

193
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:09,166
Sounds good to me.

194
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:11,083
This has helped us out
tremendously.

195
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:13,083
-Thank you.
-[HAGURO] No problem.

196
00:09:13,166 --> 00:09:15,208
Need anything else,
I'll be in the blue box.

197
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:18,875
[KYOICHI] Are those your kids?
They're so big now!

198
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:22,291
Yeah. Every time I blink,
they've grown another inch.

199
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:24,375
They sure are a handful,
but I love 'em.

200
00:09:24,458 --> 00:09:26,916
They have a good father.

201
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:27,958
They're very lucky.

202
00:09:30,208 --> 00:09:35,833
♪

203
00:09:35,916 --> 00:09:37,666
[ARATA]
So that policeman, Haguro.

204
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:40,125
-He can see the Anothers, too?
-[KYOICHI] He can.

205
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:41,708
But you're the only one
who can talk to them,

206
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:43,250
so you're not off the hook.

207
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:44,708
[ARATA chuckles]

208
00:09:45,791 --> 00:09:47,250
-It's up here.
-[faint rustling]

209
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:50,666
Okay. What's that sound?

210
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:53,666
♪

211
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:55,500
Miyako. Go check it out.

212
00:09:56,750 --> 00:10:02,666
♪

213
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:04,583
[rustling gets louder]

214
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:14,833
♪

215
00:10:14,916 --> 00:10:17,833
[ARATA screaming]

216
00:10:17,916 --> 00:10:21,958
[panting]

217
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:23,750
What's with the naked guy?

218
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:26,083
He's an Another. Not human.

219
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:28,458
That's Azukiarai. Number seven.

220
00:10:28,541 --> 00:10:30,083
I promise you he's harmless.

221
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:32,375
It's just a pain
to keep up with his location.

222
00:10:32,458 --> 00:10:34,083
We always have
to figure out where he is.

223
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:35,583
But we've done that, so...

224
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:36,833
[THEO]
There's still four more left,

225
00:10:36,916 --> 00:10:38,458
so let's keep moving.

226
00:10:38,541 --> 00:10:39,833
Hold on a sec!

227
00:10:39,916 --> 00:10:41,125
Why won't you tell me
what happened

228
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:42,875
to number one on the list?

229
00:10:42,958 --> 00:10:44,708
There wasn't anything
written down.

230
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:47,458
They were around
before World War II.

231
00:10:47,541 --> 00:10:50,000
They were a boss
in this area. I think.

232
00:10:51,875 --> 00:10:53,041
[NAKAMURA]
Those guys that came by were

233
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,750
from the ward office, right?

234
00:10:54,833 --> 00:10:56,625
-What did they want?
-[HAGURO] I didn't ask.

235
00:10:56,708 --> 00:10:58,791
I trust they had their reasons.
Huh?

236
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:02,833
What the hell's that?

237
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:04,500
-Was it a loiterer?
-Huh?

238
00:11:04,583 --> 00:11:06,958
Well, whatever it was,
it's gone.

239
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,916
Probably just
headlight reflections.

240
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,041
Must be an Another
if he can't see it.

241
00:11:12,041 --> 00:11:13,416
That must mean...
[gasps]

242
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:18,166
[bicycle clatters]

243
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:19,583
Um... uh?

244
00:11:20,958 --> 00:11:22,125
Uh, Haguro?

245
00:11:26,958 --> 00:11:28,625
♪

246
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:31,291
[THEO] There's number three.
Minerva's Owl.

247
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:34,750
Whoa, it just moved!

248
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:39,166
♪

249
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:41,833
♪

250
00:11:41,916 --> 00:11:43,500
[THEO]
This says dryad, number four,

251
00:11:43,583 --> 00:11:45,250
has no changes.

252
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:46,500
[KYOICHI]
Well, yeah, she's got roots.

253
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:47,625
She can't move.

254
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,375
[THEO]
And right over there should be

255
00:11:52,458 --> 00:11:54,541
our number five, Mezu.

256
00:11:54,625 --> 00:11:57,791
♪

257
00:11:57,875 --> 00:11:59,666
Awesome.
Just one more left.

258
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:02,208
It should be somewhere
right around here.

259
00:12:02,291 --> 00:12:03,250
Huh?

260
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:05,000
-Damn, I'm good.
-[ARATA] Huh?

261
00:12:06,041 --> 00:12:07,833
[ARATA]
Looks like a stray dog.

262
00:12:07,916 --> 00:12:09,416
[THEO]
Nope. That's a hyena.

263
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,958
What's a hyena doing
in Shinjuku?

264
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,541
[KYOICHI]
That would be Bultungin.

265
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:16,125
He came over here
with the US Army

266
00:12:16,208 --> 00:12:18,000
after the war
and then never left.

267
00:12:19,541 --> 00:12:21,250
[growls softly]

268
00:12:22,541 --> 00:12:25,208
Well, what a surprise.

269
00:12:25,291 --> 00:12:28,208
You're the Ears of Sand,
aren't you?

270
00:12:28,291 --> 00:12:31,125
I don't know how you know that,
but I am.

271
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:33,916
Good, now you can warn
the others.

272
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,166
Be careful.

273
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:39,166
Trouble is coming.

274
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:40,291
[gasps]

275
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:42,833
-Right behind you.
-Huh?

276
00:12:42,916 --> 00:12:45,541
[thudding footsteps]

277
00:12:45,625 --> 00:12:46,916
Was that a...

278
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,958
It's carrying a police officer.

279
00:12:49,041 --> 00:12:50,666
-Let's go!
-Right!

280
00:12:55,166 --> 00:12:56,250
[THEO]
You know how you hear about

281
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,000
"mysterious disappearances?"

282
00:12:58,083 --> 00:12:59,458
That's what we're witnessing
right now

283
00:12:59,541 --> 00:13:01,625
unless we do something
to save that officer.

284
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:04,041
[KYOICHI]
Uh! It's Haguro!

285
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:05,500
[THEO]
They must've made eye contact.

286
00:13:05,583 --> 00:13:06,708
That's all it takes.

287
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:11,041
[ARATA]
Where's it taking him?

288
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:12,041
[THEO]
To its territory.

289
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:14,000
Pay attention.

290
00:13:14,083 --> 00:13:16,125
You have to follow
a certain set of steps to enter.

291
00:13:16,208 --> 00:13:18,041
Sounds like a pain
to have to do that every time.

292
00:13:18,125 --> 00:13:20,083
[KYOICHI] Welcome to the world
of Anothers.

293
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:23,166
♪

294
00:13:26,875 --> 00:13:30,166
[THEO] Hold on. Kabukicho has
a Kio Inari shrine?

295
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:34,458
Shrines are supposed to be holy,
not a home base for an Another.

296
00:13:34,541 --> 00:13:38,041
♪

297
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:49,666
I think I get it now.
That's him!

298
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:50,833
The first Another.

299
00:13:50,916 --> 00:13:52,750
He's the one who disappeared.

300
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:55,125
[yawns]

301
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:56,833
[ARATA]
But what made him come back?

302
00:13:56,916 --> 00:13:59,333
And more importantly,
how do we save Haguro?

303
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:02,000
The Another doesn't seem
to be very aggressive.

304
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:03,208
[KYOICHI] Not much we can do
with him sitting

305
00:14:03,291 --> 00:14:04,375
right in front of us.

306
00:14:05,416 --> 00:14:08,000
-[ARATA] What then?
-Hmm?

307
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:10,458
-[FAIRY 1] Look, that's him!
-[FAIRY 2] It definitely is!

308
00:14:10,541 --> 00:14:12,541
Kio Gongen, I found him!

309
00:14:12,625 --> 00:14:14,333
The Ears of Sand guy's
over here!

310
00:14:14,416 --> 00:14:15,416
Seriously?

311
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:16,583
[growls]

312
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:18,958
Uh...

313
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:20,500
What happened?

314
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:23,250
Well, I know that
Another's name. So, that's done.

315
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:25,375
And, you're gonna
make us guess?

316
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,041
[ARATA]
It's, uh, Kio Gongen.

317
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:34,500
Wait, you mean
the actual god of this shrine?

318
00:14:36,291 --> 00:14:37,500
[KIO GONGEN]
What a surprise.

319
00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:39,500
I never thought
I'd see you again!

320
00:14:39,583 --> 00:14:42,541
Hah! Hello, Seimei.

321
00:14:42,625 --> 00:14:43,708
[ARATA]
I'm guessing this isn't going

322
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:44,833
to go away anytime soon.

323
00:14:44,916 --> 00:14:46,041
[laughing]

324
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:47,500
Look how mad he is!

325
00:14:47,583 --> 00:14:49,416
Sandy ears is upset!

326
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:50,500
[ARATA]
Cut it out!

327
00:14:50,583 --> 00:14:52,125
So, tell me Seimei,

328
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:54,125
what have you come here
to ask of me?

329
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:57,416
The officer! He's a friend,
please let him go!

330
00:14:59,875 --> 00:15:01,500
-You want him back?
-[ARATA] Please!

331
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:03,791
[KIO GONGEN]
I can't do that yet.

332
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:06,083
He needs to stay here
for a little longer.

333
00:15:06,166 --> 00:15:07,750
Funny story.

334
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:10,708
I think I drank a little
too much and fell asleep.

335
00:15:10,791 --> 00:15:13,083
But now that I'm awake,
we gotta throw a festival

336
00:15:13,166 --> 00:15:14,750
to make up for lost time.

337
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:17,250
A festival?
To sacrifice him?

338
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:18,208
Please don't.

339
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:22,708
I'm not gonna eat him.

340
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:24,875
I just really want
a new drinkin' buddy,

341
00:15:24,958 --> 00:15:26,291
for a hundred years or so.

342
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:28,625
-A hundred years?
-Fill us in!

343
00:15:28,708 --> 00:15:30,583
What are you two
talking about?

344
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:32,541
Sorry. He wants
to keep Haguro here

345
00:15:32,625 --> 00:15:34,833
so he can drink with him
for a hundred years.

346
00:15:34,916 --> 00:15:36,625
Anothers are such drunks.

347
00:15:36,708 --> 00:15:38,041
Please think of his family.

348
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:39,291
If you keep him for that long,

349
00:15:39,375 --> 00:15:41,000
it'll hurt them
as if he had died.

350
00:15:42,375 --> 00:15:44,166
He has two children
who need him!

351
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:45,166
Please let him go!

352
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:48,208
Hmm. Hmm!

353
00:15:48,291 --> 00:15:50,500
I mean, is it
that big of a deal?

354
00:15:51,541 --> 00:15:53,750
If I don't give him to you,
will you take him by force?

355
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:57,250
I accept your challenge, Seimei!

356
00:15:57,333 --> 00:15:59,208
-Uh...
-What did you do?

357
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:01,541
-Why is he all pissed off now?
-I don't know!

358
00:16:01,625 --> 00:16:03,666
[COYOTE]
I'm just in time!

359
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:06,000
-Are we having a drinking party?
-[chuckles]

360
00:16:06,083 --> 00:16:08,958
[KIO GONGEN]
Well, well. I remember you.

361
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,833
Listen. You don't want this.

362
00:16:11,916 --> 00:16:15,000
A festival? To do it right,
you need way more people.

363
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:17,875
[KIO GONGEN]
Hmm. I guess that's true.

364
00:16:17,958 --> 00:16:20,250
So, why not have
a drinking contest

365
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:22,041
with the three of them instead?

366
00:16:22,125 --> 00:16:23,708
If they win,
you give the man back,

367
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:26,250
and if they lose,
he stays with you.

368
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:29,375
-[KIO GONGEN laughs]
-Hey! I didn't agree to that!

369
00:16:29,458 --> 00:16:31,500
You've always been the one
who fought for everyone

370
00:16:31,583 --> 00:16:33,916
and didn't give up
until you saved them.

371
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,083
[ARATA]
Well...

372
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:38,000
So, why are you
abandoning this man?

373
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:41,625
Miyako! Remember us?
What are they saying?

374
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:43,125
Where to start.

375
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:45,250
Well, we're all having
a drinking contest with him

376
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,083
and if we win,
then he'll give us Haguro.

377
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:48,666
What? How? He's huge?

378
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:51,250
What makes you think
we could out-drink him?

379
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:53,708
[KYOICHI] I don't think
there will be an easier way.

380
00:16:53,791 --> 00:16:56,708
Tell them we accept as long as
it's something humans can drink.

381
00:16:56,791 --> 00:16:58,291
You're sure it's okay?

382
00:16:58,375 --> 00:16:59,750
[KYOICHI]
That doesn't really matter.

383
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:01,041
We don't have a choice.

384
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:03,666
♪

385
00:17:06,458 --> 00:17:09,708
[gulping]

386
00:17:09,791 --> 00:17:12,791
[inhales sharply, gulps]

387
00:17:16,708 --> 00:17:17,916
[groans]

388
00:17:20,625 --> 00:17:23,375
[gulping]

389
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:29,458
I'm done!

390
00:17:29,541 --> 00:17:30,958
[FAIRIES]
Here you go!

391
00:17:32,958 --> 00:17:34,666
[gulping]

392
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:35,791
[belches]

393
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:37,416
That looks painful.

394
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,583
This is turning out
to be worse than I thought.

395
00:17:41,750 --> 00:17:42,666
Sorry.

396
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:44,875
-[ARATA] Theo?
-[body thuds]

397
00:17:44,958 --> 00:17:46,041
[KIO GONGEN]
Oh, no,

398
00:17:46,125 --> 00:17:47,708
leaving the contest so soon?

399
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:49,875
What a pathetic loser!

400
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:51,583
[FAIRY 1]
You're the best, Mr. Gongen!

401
00:17:51,666 --> 00:17:52,791
[FAIRY 2]
Win it all!

402
00:17:52,875 --> 00:17:54,666
[COYOTE]
You're doing great, Arata!

403
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:57,458
Kohaku!
Why aren't you helping me?

404
00:17:57,541 --> 00:17:59,875
If I help you, I'm gonna have
to help everyone else

405
00:17:59,958 --> 00:18:01,541
or it wouldn't be fair.

406
00:18:01,625 --> 00:18:04,666
What do I care? I'll take on
as many of you as you want!

407
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,125
Come here.

408
00:18:06,208 --> 00:18:08,875
Call Senda and have him
send reinforcements.

409
00:18:08,958 --> 00:18:10,541
I'll handle this, don't worry.

410
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:11,666
Now hurry up!

411
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:14,000
Um... I gotta pee.

412
00:18:14,083 --> 00:18:17,166
Is that your fancy way
of saying you'll call for help?

413
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:20,541
Why not? Let's make it a party!
Bring anybody you'd like!

414
00:18:20,625 --> 00:18:23,666
Um, okay, thanks
for your hospitality.

415
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:25,000
Be right back!

416
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:28,125
[KIO GONGEN] This one seems
like he's still got

417
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:29,541
some fight in him.

418
00:18:29,625 --> 00:18:30,791
[gulps]

419
00:18:30,875 --> 00:18:32,791
[panting

420
00:18:42,791 --> 00:18:45,708
I'm impressed!
Not bad for a skinny one!

421
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:49,416
[KYOICHI] Crap.
I can't keep this up.

422
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:52,625
[breathing heavily]

423
00:18:54,916 --> 00:18:57,375
I've been running
for twenty minutes.

424
00:18:57,458 --> 00:18:58,458
[grunts in frustration]

425
00:18:58,541 --> 00:19:02,708
[gulping]

426
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:04,333
[BOTH groan]

427
00:19:04,416 --> 00:19:06,916
♪

428
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,208
Give me my next drink!
Come on!

429
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:17,750
[groaning]

430
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:19,250
[ARATA]
What the hell?

431
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,750
I'm never gonna get out of here!

432
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:24,625
[KYOICHI]
Quit making poo face at me!

433
00:19:24,708 --> 00:19:27,583
You think you're so cool
because you drink a little bit

434
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:29,208
but guess what?

435
00:19:29,291 --> 00:19:30,750
You suck at hosting

436
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:33,125
'cause my cup
does not runneth over!

437
00:19:33,208 --> 00:19:34,875
Do you even know
what it's like

438
00:19:34,958 --> 00:19:37,416
dealing with these
little bitches all day?

439
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:39,625
It's a big ol' pain
in the ass

440
00:19:39,708 --> 00:19:42,291
because I don't have
anyone to back me up!

441
00:19:49,333 --> 00:19:50,833
I saw.

442
00:19:50,916 --> 00:19:53,750
[panting]

443
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:55,250
[yells]

444
00:19:57,958 --> 00:19:59,208
[SHOJO grunts]

445
00:19:59,291 --> 00:20:00,916
[SHOJO 1]
We're out of sake, guys!

446
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,833
[SHOJO 2] We'll have to get
some more tomorrow.

447
00:20:02,916 --> 00:20:04,583
[SHOJO 1]
My buzz'll be gone by then!

448
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:06,666
[SHOJO 2] Maybe we should get
better quality sake!

449
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:08,833
[SHOJO 1] Not good enough
for you, Princess?

450
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:11,000
[SHOJO laughing]

451
00:20:11,083 --> 00:20:13,750
Hey, what do you know?
It's that Ears of Sand guy!

452
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:16,791
[SHOJO 2] Ol' rookie meat
smells like good sake!

453
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:21,833
[gulping]

454
00:20:23,166 --> 00:20:24,291
[belches]

455
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:27,375
[hiccups]

456
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:31,125
It doesn't matter
how long you stick it out.

457
00:20:31,208 --> 00:20:33,541
It's still poison
to the human body.

458
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:37,666
[gagging]

459
00:20:40,125 --> 00:20:43,291
Ki! What's up?
It's been forever!

460
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:44,791
[SHOJO 4]
Getting your wake-up drink on?

461
00:20:44,875 --> 00:20:46,791
[SHOJO 3]
Great job not inviting us!

462
00:20:46,875 --> 00:20:48,541
[SHOJO 1]
Are we not good enough for you?

463
00:20:48,625 --> 00:20:50,333
What the hell
are you doing here?

464
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:52,416
-[SHOO 5] Where's the sake?
-[SHOO 2] Move, buzzards!

465
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,708
It's time for
papa monkey's medicine.

466
00:20:56,125 --> 00:20:58,958
[gulping, slurping]

467
00:20:59,041 --> 00:21:00,041
Aah!

468
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:01,666
You were not invited!

469
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:04,000
Why are you interrupting
my festival time?

470
00:21:04,083 --> 00:21:05,916
Sounds like
somebody needs a nap.

471
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,791
Drink up, fatty.
Down the hatch!

472
00:21:07,875 --> 00:21:10,541
Hurry up! You go grab Haguro.

473
00:21:10,625 --> 00:21:12,000
I'll get Theo.

474
00:21:12,083 --> 00:21:13,166
Right!

475
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:15,125
All right, I take it back!

476
00:21:15,208 --> 00:21:17,041
Let's get ape-face-wasted!

477
00:21:18,416 --> 00:21:21,375
Now that is what I call
a party worth crashing.

478
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:23,708
So then why am I
just floating up here?

479
00:21:23,791 --> 00:21:26,625
Hey, there!
Got room for one more?

480
00:21:28,166 --> 00:21:30,125
♪

481
00:21:34,291 --> 00:21:35,250
[groans]

482
00:21:36,291 --> 00:21:38,000
[panting]

483
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,708
[KYOICHI]
How are you feeling, Rookie?

484
00:21:40,791 --> 00:21:43,625
[ARATA] Like I want to go home
and take a hot bath.

485
00:21:43,708 --> 00:21:47,708
[THEO slurring] Reports-es.
Gotta write reports-es.

486
00:21:47,791 --> 00:21:51,291
♪

487
00:21:51,375 --> 00:21:54,958
[BULTINGIN] See? I told you
there was trouble.

488
00:21:55,041 --> 00:21:56,583
[laughing]

489
00:21:56,666 --> 00:21:59,833
♪

490
00:21:59,916 --> 00:22:01,083
[KYOICHI]
Hurry it up!

491
00:22:01,166 --> 00:22:02,666
Uh. I'm coming!

492
00:22:03,708 --> 00:22:05,166
Lesson learned.

493
00:22:05,250 --> 00:22:07,000
Anothers are a pain.

494
00:22:07,083 --> 00:22:08,791
[THEO]
Too many reports-es!

495
00:22:08,875 --> 00:22:09,958
[groans]

